{{year-header}}

==February==
* '''[[13 February|13]]''' - [[Mary Jane Stow]] dies.
==March==
* '''?''' - Earliest "evidence" of Tolkien working on "fairy language".
==April==
* '''?''' - [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] writes the poem ''[[Goblin Feet]]''.
==June==
* '''[[10 June|10]]''' - Exams start at [[Oxford University]]. Because of [[Great War|the war]], only Tolkien and 24 others remain in the entire University. Tolkien passes.
* '''[[28 June|28]]''' -  Tolkien applies at the Oxford recruiting office to join the army.
* '''[[28 June|28]]''' - [[Przemyslaw Mroczkowski]], scholar and friend of [[J.R.R. Tolkien]], is born.
* '''?''' - Tolkien is awarded First Class Honours degree in English Language and Literature.
==July==
* '''[[15 July|15]]''' - Tolkien is commissioned as a second lieutenant of the 13th Battalion Lancashire Fusiliers, and begins training at Bedford.
==September==
* '''[[25 September|25]]''' - The Big Four of the [[T.C.B.S.]] - Tolkien, [[Geoffrey Bache Smith|Smith]], [[Christopher Wiseman|Wiseman]] and [[Robert Gilson|Gilson]] - have their last meeting.
==October==
* '''[[4 October|4]]''' - Translator [[Tore Zetterholm]] is born.
==November==
*'''?''' - Tolkien writes his earliest version of ''[[The Trees of Kortirion]]''.
* '''[[21 November|21]]''' -  G.B. Smith is shipped to France.
* '''[[26 November|26]]''' -  Tolkien writes [[Letter 3]] with a copy of ''Kortirion'' to [[Edith Bratt]] from Rugeley Camp, Staffordshire.

==December==
*'''?''' - Tolkien might have written the poem ''[[Eruman beneath the Stars|Habbanan beneath the Stars]]''.
==?==
* '''?''' - The poem "[[Goblin Feet]]" is published in ''[[Oxford Poetry|Oxford Poetry 1915]]''.
